{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":846,"record_hash":"sha256:ea525094d3bf840aae84054fecb746e946b756a440118859f5787099d81c2566","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:32:38.347Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Dry-run still creates/migrates GitMeta storage\\\" body=\\\"`write_capture` opens a writable GitMeta session and reads through that handle before checking `plan.dry_run`. In git-meta-lib, `Session::open` opens or creates `.git/git-meta.sqlite`, configures WAL, and runs migrations, so `--dry-run` can mutate local GitMeta state even when it skips the later `set`/`list_push` calls. Use a read-only/no-create path for dry-run hash-set reads, or treat a missing store as empty, and add a test asserting no `.git/git-meta.sqlite*` appears after dry-run.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=44 end=59 priority=2 confidence=0.91}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Transcript append is not idempotent after partial failure\\\" body=\\\"The transcript envelope is appended before its hash is recorded in `transcript-record-hashes`. If the process exits or `set_add` fails after `list_push` succeeds, the next capture will not see the hash and will append the same envelope again. Make the list append and hash update atomic, or rebuild/check transcript hashes from existing envelope records before appending.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=64 end=77 priority=2 confidence=0.87}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Duplicate records in one snapshot are planned twice\\\" body=\\\"`compute_write_plan` checks each record only against the pre-existing GitMeta hash sets; it does not update an in-memory set as records are selected. If the same raw JSONL record appears twice in the current snapshot, both entries are planned as new, and `--include-transcript` will append duplicate envelopes in one run. Track planned hashes while iterating and add a fixture with duplicate lines.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=105 end=118 priority=2 confidence=0.84}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] POC docs still recommend publishable agent keys\\\" body=\\\"The data-model doc lists `agent:provider`, `agent:model`, and `agent:session-id` as minimum POC writes, while the requirements and implementation contract say first-POC data should stay under `meta:local:gitbutler:*`. Because non-`meta:local:` keys are eligible for GitMeta serialization, this doc conflict is a privacy footgun for the next patch. Move `agent:*` writes to a clearly future-only section and align `architecture.md:226` plus `capture-workflow.md:49` with local-only POC behavior.\\\" file=\\\"[REDACTED:entropy].md\\\" start=45 end=52 priority=2 confidence=0.9}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Missing-session path hash uses lossy path text\\\" body=\\\"When Codex has no session id, the session key is derived from `source_path.to_string_lossy()`. Distinct non-UTF-8 transcript paths can collapse to the same replacement-character string, which can merge unrelated missing-session captures under one key. Hash a deterministic byte representation of the canonical path instead, and keep the displayed/stored path handling separate.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs\\\" start=107 end=108 priority=3 confidence=0.72}\\n\\nI did not find code paths that call GitMeta `serialize`, push, fetch, sync, or materialize from the new capture command. Hash-set reads/writes use `get_value` plus `MetaValue::Set` and `set_add`, and the implemented write keys are `meta:local:*` only. I did not run tests; this was a review-only pass.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:32:38.347Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Dry-run still creates/migrates GitMeta storage\\\" body=\\\"`write_capture` opens a writable GitMeta session and reads through that handle before checking `plan.dry_run`. In git-meta-lib, `Session::open` opens or creates `.git/git-meta.sqlite`, configures WAL, and runs migrations, so `--dry-run` can mutate local GitMeta state even when it skips the later `set`/`list_push` calls. Use a read-only/no-create path for dry-run hash-set reads, or treat a missing store as empty, and add a test asserting no `.git/git-meta.sqlite*` appears after dry-run.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=44 end=59 priority=2 confidence=0.91}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Transcript append is not idempotent after partial failure\\\" body=\\\"The transcript envelope is appended before its hash is recorded in `transcript-record-hashes`. If the process exits or `set_add` fails after `list_push` succeeds, the next capture will not see the hash and will append the same envelope again. Make the list append and hash update atomic, or rebuild/check transcript hashes from existing envelope records before appending.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=64 end=77 priority=2 confidence=0.87}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Duplicate records in one snapshot are planned twice\\\" body=\\\"`compute_write_plan` checks each record only against the pre-existing GitMeta hash sets; it does not update an in-memory set as records are selected. If the same raw JSONL record appears twice in the current snapshot, both entries are planned as new, and `--include-transcript` will append duplicate envelopes in one run. Track planned hashes while iterating and add a fixture with duplicate lines.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=105 end=118 priority=2 confidence=0.84}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] POC docs still recommend publishable agent keys\\\" body=\\\"The data-model doc lists `agent:provider`, `agent:model`, and `agent:session-id` as minimum POC writes, while the requirements and implementation contract say first-POC data should stay under `meta:local:gitbutler:*`. Because non-`meta:local:` keys are eligible for GitMeta serialization, this doc conflict is a privacy footgun for the next patch. Move `agent:*` writes to a clearly future-only section and align `architecture.md:226` plus `capture-workflow.md:49` with local-only POC behavior.\\\" file=\\\"[REDACTED:entropy].md\\\" start=45 end=52 priority=2 confidence=0.9}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Missing-session path hash uses lossy path text\\\" body=\\\"When Codex has no session id, the session key is derived from `source_path.to_string_lossy()`. Distinct non-UTF-8 transcript paths can collapse to the same replacement-character string, which can merge unrelated missing-session captures under one key. Hash a deterministic byte representation of the canonical path instead, and keep the displayed/stored path handling separate.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs\\\" start=107 end=108 priority=3 confidence=0.72}\\n\\nI did not find code paths that call GitMeta `serialize`, push, fetch, sync, or materialize from the new capture command. Hash-set reads/writes use `get_value` plus `MetaValue::Set` and `set_add`, and the implemented write keys are `meta:local:*` only. I did not run tests; this was a review-only pass.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}